templates.name: Search phrase 3
templates.text: Get all EC2 instance with CVEs of severity $type
templates.cypher:
MATCH (ec2:`EC2Instance`)-[hp:HAS_PRODUCT]->(p:Product)
WITH ec2, p, hp
MATCH (p)-[hc:HAS_CVE]->(cve:Vulnerability {v2severity: $type})
RETURN ec2, p, hp, cve, hc

params.name: $type
params.cypher: MATCH (v:Vulnerability) where v.v2severity is not null RETURN distinct v.v2severity

templates.name: Get all EC2 instance with CVEs
templates.text: Get all EC2 instance with CVEs
templates.cypher:
MATCH (ec2:`EC2Instance`)<-[hp:INSTALLED_ON]->(p:ProductVersion)
WITH ec2, p, hp
MATCH (p)-[hc:`VERSION_HAS_VULNERABILITY`]->(cve:Vulnerability)
RETURN ec2, p, hp, cve, hc;

templates.name: Search phrase that returns a sample of your data
templates.cypher: MATCH (n) OPTIONAL MATCH p=(n)--() RETURN p, n LIMIT 100
